/span\u003E, so it was back to the computer.\u00A0 So far, this is about as long as will work. I had 19 at one point, but the tail just swished around like an irritated cat.\u00A0 As it was, it took a lot of tweaking and a lot of practicing to get it into the air and then stay airborne.\u00A0 Lots of explosions took place.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI crashed this so many times on takeoff, I was not even thinking about landing it; I assumed it was near impossible. Then after a recovery (about the 2:00 mark in the video) I found myself over land.\u00A0 So, I put down the gear on a lark. And it worked!!!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, a new genre of aircraft: \u003Cstrong\u003Ecentipede\u00A0planes. \u003C/strong\u003EOr perhaps \u003Cstrong\u003Ecaterpillar planes?\u00A0\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks to \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/153808-kergarin/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022153808\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/153808-kergarin/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Kergarin\u003C/a\u003E, whose \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/184892-breaking-ground-walker-speed-challenge/\u0026amp;tab=comments#comment-3608398\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EWalker Speed Challenge\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0got me thinking along these lines (that is, thinking about long things with lots of hinges).\u00A0 And also to this builder on KerbalX, whose centipede was a huge inspiration\u00A0\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/SWDennis/Centipede-1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/SWDennis/Centipede-1\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis DLC has changed everything.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[snip]\n\u003C/p\