e-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221560277311\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022adsii1970\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, adsii1970 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI see a build in your future, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148725-just-jim/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022148725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/148725-just-jim/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Just Jim\u003C/a\u003E!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNaaa.... this is all \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181256-klapaucius/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022181256\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181256-klapaucius/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Klapaucius\u003C/a\u003E!\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am really, really impressed how you\u0027re using the sequencer to maneuver it, and how well it responds. That is genius!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-11T20:08:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223616628\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221560280063\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Just Jim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Just Jim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNaaa.... this is all \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181256-klapaucius/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022181256\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181256-klapaucius/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Klapaucius\u003C/a\u003E!\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am really, really impressed how you\u0027re using the sequencer to maneuver it, and how well it responds. That is genius!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for the kind words.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it comes from video editing. You wouldn\u0027t know it\u00A0because most of my KSP edits are hastily thrown together, but I actually have\u00A0made a film and have spent a lot of time in Adobe Premiere. I don\u0027t know if you are familiar with video editing, but all programs use some variation of a keyframe editor (as also do digital audio workstations such as Logic Pro X or 3D motion like Blender or Unity), which is exactly what the controller is, so this is really familiar territory.\u00A0 It\u0027s just like scrubbing a playhead to test an edit.\u00A0 This biggest frustration is that the controller is quite limited compared to what I am used to.\u00A0 I started a thread on this if you are interested:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Duh , of course you are familiar with all this. You are Squad staff.... I need to pay more attention to things\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:o\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon2.png\u0022 title=\u0022:o\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7498390148\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/185156-dlc-controller-workflow-suggestions/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3612355\u0026amp;embedComment=3612355\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-3612355\u0022 style=\u0022height:307px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-11T23:36:46Z\u0022 title=\u002206/11/2019 11:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 11, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Klapaucius\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-11T21:25:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223616502\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221560269129\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196731\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SecondChance\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, SecondChance said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh if I was on PC and not PS4 i would give it a go! This DLC is gonna force me to get a decent rig i think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI bet rentry would be scary!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe issue is past a certain speed you get a resonance frequency going. If you look at the video at 2:15, it started sine waving badly. The solution was to cut the power and turn the X-Axis controller--putting a bend in it side-to-side seems to counteract the up and down flexing.\u00A0 I don\u0027t know if in KSP physics it increases with speed or whether there is a threshold past which you are okay, but at the moment, it will shake itself apart if I don\u0027t take immediate measures.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-11T21:25:58Z\u0022 title=\u002206/11/2019 09:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 11, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Klapaucius\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-11T22:15:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt did not fly well, but it flew. I figured out part of my problem on the tail end, so then I thought, MOAR segments. Here is 30.\u00A0 The pilot survived.\u00A0 The third that was left after crashing wanted to continue on...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022q3UtzYt.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/q3UtzYt.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002209CL3Kh.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/09CL3Kh.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022FZLYbAg.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/FZLYbAg.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-11T22:23:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223616378\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221560254907\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Klapaucius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Klapaucius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t even build a regular \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E...\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:blush:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_embarrassed.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:blush:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy inner aerodynamicist weeps every time I open your KerbalX page. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-12T01:37:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223616664\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185360\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221560283712\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Klapaucius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Klapaucius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Duh , of course you are familiar with all this. You are Squad staff.... I need to pay more attention to things\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhhahahaha...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve\u00A0got some experience\u00A0with Lightwave 3D, if you\u0027re familiar with it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just never really considered using the sequencer quite the way you do, as a flight controller... I suppose that\u0027s a good way of putting it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd it just looks really cool flying around!!!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-12T01:38:36Z\u0022 title=\u002206/12/2019 01:38  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 12, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Just Jim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-12T01:40:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen things go wrong, they take on epic proportions. It\u0027s like a scene from a Japanese monster movie:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022uYKI6zI.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/uYKI6zI.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022jV1cXLZ.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/jV1cXLZ.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-12T01:41:06Z\u0022 title=\u002206/12/2019 01:41  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 12, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Klapaucius\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-12T02:48:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is now up on KerbalX if anyone wants to have a go at it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Klapaucius/Milo-Centipede-Plane\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Klapaucius/Milo-Centipede-Plane\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}